00:59:21.305 --> 00:59:24.760
see the electronic trading
system.

00:59:24.760 --> 00:59:31.450
Of course, there are many such
books now that are available.

00:59:38.210 --> 00:59:42.008
The dealer--the specialist on
the exchange also has his

00:59:42.008 --> 00:59:46.228
own--his or her own--bid-asked
spread, which is also an offer

00:59:46.228 --> 00:59:49.594
to buy or sell on the exchange.
Incidentally,

00:59:49.594 --> 00:59:52.448
Island would only allow one
kind of order,

00:59:52.448 --> 00:59:55.503
at least originally.
It was only limit orders

00:59:55.503 --> 00:59:59.196
because they didn't--they had a
system where you had to put it

00:59:59.196 --> 01:00:02.829
onto their book and everything
had to appear on the book,

01:00:02.829 --> 01:00:06.210
so it was just a limit order
book originally.

01:00:06.210 --> 01:00:12.573
The history of this--I guess
one thing I wanted to--what I

01:00:12.573 --> 01:00:18.489
was leading up to is that the
ECNs are history now.

01:00:18.489 --> 01:00:21.070
They've been generally merged
and acquired.

01:00:21.070 --> 01:00:24.337
Notably, the New York Stock
Exchange, which has been the

01:00:24.337 --> 01:00:28.390
holdout doing floor trading,
bought Archipelago because

01:00:28.390 --> 01:00:33.629
Archipelago was growing so fast
doing this kind of electronic

01:00:33.629 --> 01:00:36.550
trading;
it was really catching on.

01:00:36.550 --> 01:00:41.575
New York Stock Exchange began
to worry that it was starting to

01:00:41.575 --> 01:00:45.124
get behind the times.
The New York Stock--these

01:00:45.124 --> 01:00:49.095
things, which were started by
kids--young college students in

01:00:49.095 --> 01:00:53.198
the late â€˜90s--just grew
so fast and they got so big that

01:00:53.198 --> 01:00:57.367
Archipelago was starting to look
like it was going to get bigger

01:00:57.367 --> 01:01:01.458
than New York Stock Exchange.
So, finally New York Stock

01:01:01.458 --> 01:01:05.400
Exchange merged with them and
they changed the name after 200

01:01:05.400 --> 01:01:09.525
years in business.
They changed the name to NYSE

01:01:09.525 --> 01:01:14.070
Archa--Archa is short for
Archipelago Exchange.

01:01:14.070 --> 01:01:17.539
That didn't last long;
they changed their name again.

01:01:17.539 --> 01:01:21.804
They just merged--New York
Stock Exchange merged with the

01:01:21.804 --> 01:01:25.536
European Stock Exchange,
Euronext, and so now it's

01:01:25.536 --> 01:01:29.973
called NYSE Euronext.
Everything happened so fast and

01:01:29.973 --> 01:01:34.751
it seems fast to me.
The New York Stock Exchange is

01:01:34.751 --> 01:01:39.241
in the process,
we think, of merging with the

01:01:39.241 --> 01:01:45.159
American Stock Exchange and
that's happening right now.

01:01:45.159 --> 01:01:47.486
[NYSE Euronext announced on
